block intro-caption
  :marked
    Photo: [John Brawley/Flickr](https://www.flickr.com/photos/johnbrawley/1594605606)

block intro-description
  :marked
    The 2019–2020 budget provides $38.7 billion for the Defence Department.
    Both major parties have committed to increase spending to 2% of GDP. There
    has been significant focus on growing the domestic defence industry,
    particularly ship-building. In January 2018 the Turnbull government
    committed to making Australia a “top ten” global defence exporter.

