              The bipartisan commitment to higher defence spending is welcome,
              but Australia wastes too much money on non-essential
              capabilities.

              China’s maritime power is growing and America’s is declining.
              Rising Chinese influence in Australia’s neighbourhood is
              inevitable, but our defence focus should be on ensuring that
              Southeast Asia and the Pacific can never be dominated by Chinese
              military power.

              Australia also needs to think about how it manages competition
              with China if America decides it does not want to compete. Higher
              spending would be necessary in those circumstances, but not
              sufficient. We need closer friendships in the region, and there
              is no more important partner than Indonesia.

